  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "fpmLthYUYCDdcJywfllBVxE48rA=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:30.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\n`CompositeChannelFactory` implements `IChannelFactory` but dispatches `instance()` calls to registered sub-factories keyed by `config.type` (e.g., `\"gql\"`, `\"swarm\"`).\n\n## Evidence\nThe source defines a `factories: Map<string, IChannelFactory>` with `register(type, factory)`. On `instance()`, it looks up `config.type` and delegates, throwing if the type is unregistered.\n\n```typescript\nconst factory = this.factories.get(config.type);\nif (!factory) throw new Error(`Unknown channel type \"${config.type}\"...`);\nreturn factory.instance(remoteId, remoteName, config, cursorStorage, collectionId, filter, operationIndex);\n```\n\n## Why this pattern\nThe reactor exposes only one `IChannelFactory` slot per instance. Without the composite, adding Swarm would require monkey-patching or forking the reactor. The composite is a clean strategy/registry pattern that leaves the reactor interface untouched.\n\n## Source\n`adapter/src/channel/composite-factory.ts`; Swarm Channel Architecture, \"CompositeChannelFactory\" section.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:30.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:30.000Z"
    }
  },
